-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Refiner Mol Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-20T10:34:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index weakened 0.3
percent to 17,251.90 percent by 12:29 p.m. in Budapest, trimming
its weekly gain to 1.4 percent.  The following are among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, snapped four
days of gains as oil fell from a nine-week high. The stock
declined as much as 0.6 percent and last traded 0.1 percent
lower at 16,900 forint.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)   Hungary’s largest lender, slid 0.5
percent to 3,433 forint. European stocks dropped, trimming a
seventh straight week of gains.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
